{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/2017/what-is-web-accessibility","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Accessibility means letting the user navigate and interact with a website by any means. Let it be a keyboard, a mouse or people with disabilities or impairments.</p>\n<h2 id=\"web-accessibility\" style=\"position:relative;\">Web Accessibility<a href=\"#web-accessibility\" aria-label=\"web accessibility permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h2>\n<p>Let us learn what is web accessibility by starting with a simple html button. We will style both the <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;div&gt;</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;button&gt;</code> tag to look like a button.</p>\n<h3 id=\"button\" style=\"position:relative;\">Button<a href=\"#button\" aria-label=\"button permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- div used as button --></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>btn<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Click Me<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- actual button --></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>button</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">class</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>btn<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Click Me<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<p>We will inspect and see how the user might use your website, follow the below steps.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>Keyboard</b> - <i>Try to focus the below buttons using <kbd>tab</kbd> key in your keyboard.</i></li>\n<li><b>Mouse</b> - <i>Try to click the below buttons using mouse.</i></li>\n<li><b>Voice Over</b> - <i>Turn on voice over by pressing <kbd>command</kbd> + <kbd>f5</kbd> in <code class=\"language-text\">mac</code> and click the below buttons.</i></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"btn\">Click Me</div>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">Not focusable</code>, because of using a <code class=\"language-text\">div</code> tag as button</li>\n</ul>\n<p><button class=\"btn\">Click Me</button></p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"highlighter-rouge focusable\">Focusable</code>, because it's an actual <code class=\"language-text\">button</code></li>\n</ul>\n<iframe width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/IaL4nBgdxeM\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n<p><a href=\"https://output.jsbin.com/qezeca\" target=\"_blank\">Demo Link</a></p>\n<h3 id=\"images\" style=\"position:relative;\">Images<a href=\"#images\" aria-label=\"images permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Let's imagine, our user is going to read out loud on our website. Using <code class=\"language-text\">alt</code> text, a user can find what is that image is. That's what <code class=\"language-text\">alt</code> attribute is for.</p>\n<p><b>Example: </b></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token comment\">&lt;!-- img tag with alt attribute --></span>\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>img</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>sample.jpg<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">alt</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>Sample image<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"forms\" style=\"position:relative;\">Forms<a href=\"#forms\" aria-label=\"forms permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Consider a <code class=\"language-text\">screen reader</code> is going to fill a form on your website, but the user needs to know the information about the form.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"html\"><pre class=\"language-html\"><code class=\"language-html\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>label</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">for</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>email<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span>Email<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>label</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">></span></span> <span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>input</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">type</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>email<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">id</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>email<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">required</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">/></span></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3 id=\"example\" style=\"position:relative;\">Example:<a href=\"#example\" aria-label=\"example permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>Use voice over for below inputs and inspect the input tag.</p>\n<h4>Without label &#x26; required attribute:</h4>\n<div>\n  <h5 class=\"center\">Example Form (No Label)</h5>\n  <form class=\"post-form-example\">\n    <span>Name</span>\n    <input type=\"text\"/>\n    <span>Email</span>\n    <input type=\"email\"/>\n    <input type=\"submit\" value=\"submit\"/>\n  </form>\n</div>\n<p>Above form doesn't tell the user that, what kind of an input he is going to fill nor its required or not. It will voiceover that it's just an input.</p>\n<h4>With label &#x26; required attribute:</h4>\n<p>We don't want our user to submit the form without filling required fields. That's where <code class=\"highlighter-rouge\">label</code> element <code class=\"highlighter-rouge\">required</code> attribute comes in.</p>\n<div>\n  <h5 class=\"center\">Example Form (With Label)</h5>\n  <form class=\"post-form-example\">\n    <label for=\"name\">Name</label>\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"name\" required/>\n    <label for=\"email\">Email</label>\n    <input type=\"email\" id=\"email\" required/>\n    <input type=\"submit\" value=\"submit\"/>\n  </form>\n</div>\n<p>Above form will voice over the user about the <code class=\"highlighter-rouge\">input</code> field and whether its <code class=\"highlighter-rouge\">required</code> or not.</p>\n<h3 id=\"conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\">Conclusion<a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<p>As a developer I recommend my fellow developers to consider all kinds of user and accessibility in mind while developing an application or a website. Thanks for reading my post. Catch you in my next post.</p>\n<h3 id=\"references\" style=\"position:relative;\">References<a href=\"#references\" aria-label=\"references permalink\" class=\"blog-post-heading-link after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/WAI/intro/accessibility.php\" target=\"_blank\">What is Web Accessibility</a> - WAI</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNYkxOF6rcICWx0C9LVWWVqvHlYJyqw7g\" target=\"_blank\">A11ycasts\n</a> - Rob Dodson</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/GoogleChrome/accessibility-developer-tools/wiki/Audit-Rules\" target=\"_blank\">Accessibility developer tools</a> - Chrome Developer Tools</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"Mar 07, 2017","updated":null,"slug":"/blog/2017/what-is-web-accessibility","title":"What is accessibility?","description":null,"relative":null},"fields":{"readingTime":{"text":"3 min read"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2017/what-is-web-accessibility"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3633477710"]}